Cascading Scala Maven Example
tommy@chheng.com
-
This is a sample project to help you get started with Cascading using Scala and Maven.

To get started, you can clone this project:
git clone git@github.com/tc/cascading-scala-maven-example.git

To build a JAR file to use with a hadoop cluster, type:
mvn package

Download cascading from http://cascading.org
In the root folder, there should be a cascading-core-X.X.X.jar and a cascading-xmlX.X.X.jar in the lib folder. 

Install these into your local maven repo.
mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=cascading -DartifactId=cascading-core -Dversion=1.1.2 -Dpackaging=jar -Dfile=cascading-core-1.1.2.jar
mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=cascading -DartifactId=cascading-xml -Dversion=1.1.2 -Dpackaging=jar -Dfile=cascading-xml-1.1.2.jar

Other dependencies to install from the cascading lib folder:
mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=org.jgrapht -DartifactId=jgrapht -Dversion=0.8.1 -Dpackaging=jar -Dfile=jgrapht-jdk1.6.jar

Download hadoop and install hadoop into your local maven repo as well.
mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=org.apache.hadoop -DartifactId=hadoop-core -Dversion=0.20.2 -Dpackaging=jar -Dfile=hadoop-core-0.20.2.jar


